body: Anita is getting pain in her hip and leg/s. It might be sciatica, or joint inflammation. Walking seems to help a little, so we are doing an easier walk today
To the Club for dinner etc. I had fish, chips and salad (no dressing) from the cafe. We had a big breakfast this morning
Collected equipment from the lab and headed down to the project office to test the Asset Tracker against Nexus.

I parked beside the road in a spot where we could position the chairs and the camp table. I had the bigger camping chairs since there was the room to carry them.

We brought the electric kettle to make a cup of hot tea. Anita had a danish to with hers.
Just stopped for a quick toilet break.
This mornings plan was to only do a short walk up to the coffee shop and then go back home. We did stop for a while in the nearby park.

My convertible cargo pants had a big rip in them, so we are here at Anaconda to see if they have suitable replacements. I ended up trying on six pants! The brands were North Face, Mountain Designs and Columbia.

I settled on two pairs from the Columbia brand. They are size 36, but feel like 35, so were a better fit than the other brands.
Took the WRX for a drive to charge up the battery which was not liking the cold and wouldnâ€™t start earlier.

After coming back hoe in the WRX, I parked it on the street behind RevMans unregistered Holden Berlina V8. Then I took the Tesla for a similar drive, although this time there was less traffic on the freeway so was able to take the drive through the Mount Cotton Area.
We dropped Katherine off at rehearsals at the loading zone outside the old museum.
Kiara is COVID-19+, so I asked Laura if she is able to work tomorrow evening as well. She agreed!
Looking for cheaper petrol. The price around this area is generally lower than most other places in Brisbane.
The battery in the phone went dead at the crossing. The headphones in the helmet stopped and shutdown in response.
